### TEST API GATEWAY (Using REST Client plugin in VSCode)

@gateway = http://localhost:3000

### 1. Test Without Auth -> Should block access to protected route (Booking)
GET {{gateway}}/api/v1/booking/123

### 2. Test Invalid Payload to Auth (Zod Validation Gateway Drop)
POST {{gateway}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "not-an-email",
  "password": "123" 
}
# Expected: 400 Bad Request, Validation Failed

### 3. Test Proxy to Auth Login (Assuming Auth Service returns a token)
POST {{gateway}}/api/v1/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

### 4. Provide Token for subsequent requests
# Replace with real token obtained
@token = eyJhbGciOiJIUzI1NiIsInR5cCI...

### 5. Test Valid Booking Request with Token (RBAC + ABAC)
GET {{gateway}}/api/v1/booking/user/1
Authorization: Bearer {{token}}

### 6. Test WebSocket proxy testing
# Since this is an HTTP file, use a WebSocket client (like Postman or wscat) to connect to ws://localhost:3000/ws/ride

### 7. Test Global Rate Limiter
# Keep sending this request rapidly to see 429 Too Many Requests response
GET {{gateway}}/api/v1/auth/some-public-endpoint
